Sentencas: We prepared LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 with 0.2 <= x <= 0.6 and 0.1 <= y <= 0.4 (LNCF) powder and investigated its characteristics as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To investigate the crystal structure of LNCF, we analyzed LNCF powder using X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure of LNCF belongs to a rhombohedral system.
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: High total conductivity above 100 S cm(-1) at 1073 K was obtained for LNCF.
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When x in this system is 0.6, the total conductivity at 1073 K is more than 500 S cm(-1).
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This conductivity is greater than that of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) between 323 and 1323 K. The average coefficient of thermal expansion of LNCF is smaller than that of LSCF.
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To investigate the chemical stability against Cr2O3, we heated LNCF-Cr2O3, LSCF-Cr2O3 and La0.6Sr0.4CoO3 (LSC)-Cr2O3 powder mixtures at 1073 K for 0-1000 h. We found that LNCF powder was less reactive with Cr2O3 than LSCF and LSC powder.
Titulo: Characterization of LaNixCoyFe1-x-yO3 as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells
